From b0bee269d2ccbb0965eb09093fee9e601f6d0263 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vignesh Viswanathan <viswanat@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 13 Jun 2025 01:09:39 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] drivers: clk: qcom: ipq: Set CLK_IGNORE_UNUSED for all PCIe
 clocks

For Early Coldboot Calibration support, U-boot enumerates and starts
calibration on the PCIe EPs like QCN9224. Kernel will gate the
PCIe clocks till the PCIe driver is probed, which will interrupt the
calibration happening on the PCIe EP.

Set CLK_IGNORE_UNUSED flag for all PCIe clocks so that kernel will not
gate these clocks and calibration can happen in parallel to kernel
bootup.

Change-Id: I9b74b554180977930461bb9fc8469f5626c6389e
Signed-off-by: Vignesh Viswanathan <viswanat@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
